claims:
1.一种封装结构，包括：1. A packaging structure, comprising:


         电路元件；Circuit components;


         第一半导体管芯及第二半导体管芯，位于所述电路元件上；A first semiconductor die and a second semiconductor die are located on the circuit element;


         散热元件，连接到所述第一半导体管芯，所述第一半导体管芯位于所述电路元件与所述散热元件之间，其中所述第一半导体管芯的第一厚度与所述散热元件的第三厚度之和实质上等于所述第二半导体管芯的第二厚度；以及a heat sink element connected to the first semiconductor die, the first semiconductor die being located between the circuit element and the heat sink element, wherein a sum of a first thickness of the first semiconductor die and a third thickness of the heat sink element is substantially equal to a second thickness of the second semiconductor die; and


         绝缘包封体，包封所述第一半导体管芯、所述第二半导体管芯及所述散热元件，其中所述散热元件的表面与所述绝缘包封体的表面实质上齐平。An insulating encapsulation body encapsulates the first semiconductor die, the second semiconductor die, and the heat dissipation element, wherein a surface of the heat dissipation element is substantially flush with a surface of the insulating encapsulation body.

10.一种制造封装结构的方法，包括：10. A method for manufacturing a packaging structure, comprising:


         提供连接有散热元件的第一半导体管芯；providing a first semiconductor die having a heat sink element attached thereto;


         提供第二半导体管芯；providing a second semiconductor die;


         将所述第一半导体管芯、所述第二半导体管芯及所述散热元件包封在绝缘包封体中；以及encapsulating the first semiconductor die, the second semiconductor die, and the heat dissipation element in an insulating encapsulation; and


         将所述绝缘包封体平坦化，以使所述绝缘包封体暴露出所述散热元件，其中所述第一半导体管芯的第一厚度与所述散热元件的第三厚度之和实质上等于所述第二半导体管芯的第二厚度。The insulating encapsulation is planarized so that the insulating encapsulation exposes the heat dissipation element, wherein a sum of a first thickness of the first semiconductor die and a third thickness of the heat dissipation element is substantially equal to a second thickness of the second semiconductor die.

15.根据权利要求10所述的方法，还包括：15. The method according to claim 10, further comprising:


         提供其中具有多个穿孔的中介体；providing an interposer having a plurality of perforations therein;


         在将所述第一半导体管芯及所述第二半导体管芯包封在所述绝缘包封体中之前，通过倒装芯片接合将所述第一半导体管芯及所述第二半导体管芯设置在所述中介体上；before encapsulating the first semiconductor die and the second semiconductor die in the insulating encapsulant, disposing the first semiconductor die and the second semiconductor die on the interposer by flip chip bonding;


         在将所述绝缘包封体平坦化之后，将所述中介体图案化以显露出所述多个穿孔；After planarizing the insulating encapsulation, patterning the interposer to reveal the plurality of through-holes;


         在被显露出的所述多个穿孔上形成多个连接件，所述中介体夹置在所述绝缘包封体与所述多个连接件之间；以及forming a plurality of connectors on the exposed plurality of through holes, wherein the interposer is sandwiched between the insulating enclosure and the plurality of connectors; and


         通过所述中介体的所述多个连接件，将所述第一半导体管芯与所述第二半导体管芯接合在具有多个导电端子的电路结构上，所述电路衬底夹置在所述多个导电端子与所述多个连接件之间。The first semiconductor die and the second semiconductor die are bonded to a circuit structure having a plurality of conductive terminals through the plurality of connectors of the interposer, and the circuit substrate is sandwiched between the plurality of conductive terminals and the plurality of connectors.

17.一种制造封装结构的方法，包括：17. A method for manufacturing a packaging structure, comprising:


         提供至少一个第一半导体管芯及至少一个第二半导体管芯；providing at least one first semiconductor die and at least one second semiconductor die;


         在所述至少一个第一半导体管芯的表面上设置虚设元件，所述至少一个第一半导体管芯位于所述虚设元件之上；providing a dummy element on a surface of the at least one first semiconductor die, the at least one first semiconductor die being located above the dummy element;


         将所述至少一个第一半导体管芯、所述至少一个第二半导体管芯及所述虚设元件包封在绝缘包封体中；encapsulating the at least one first semiconductor die, the at least one second semiconductor die, and the dummy element in an insulating encapsulation;


         将所述绝缘包封体平坦化，以使所述绝缘包封体的表面暴露出所述虚设元件；planarizing the insulating enclosure so that the dummy element is exposed on the surface of the insulating enclosure;


         移除所述虚设元件，以在所述绝缘包封体中形成凹槽；以及removing the dummy element to form a recess in the insulating enclosure; and


         在所述至少一个第一半导体管芯上及在所述凹槽中设置散热元件，其中所述至少一个第一半导体管芯的第一厚度与所述散热元件的第三厚度之和实质上等于所述至少一个第二半导体管芯的第二厚度。A heat dissipation element is disposed on the at least one first semiconductor die and in the recess, wherein a sum of a first thickness of the at least one first semiconductor die and a third thickness of the heat dissipation element is substantially equal to a second thickness of the at least one second semiconductor die.

20.根据权利要求17所述的方法，还包括：20. The method of claim 17, further comprising:


         提供其中具有多个穿孔的中介体；providing an interposer having a plurality of perforations therein;


         在所述至少一个第一半导体管芯上设置所述虚设元件之前，通过倒装芯片接合将所述至少一个第一半导体管芯及所述至少一个第二半导体管芯设置在所述中介体上；Before disposing the dummy element on the at least one first semiconductor die, disposing the at least one first semiconductor die and the at least one second semiconductor die on the interposer by flip chip bonding;


         在将所述绝缘包封体平坦化之后，将所述中介体图案化以显露出所述多个穿孔；After planarizing the insulating encapsulation, patterning the interposer to reveal the plurality of through-holes;


         在被显露出的所述多个穿孔上形成多个连接件，所述中介体夹置在所述绝缘包封体与所述多个连接件之间；以及forming a plurality of connectors on the exposed plurality of through holes, wherein the interposer is sandwiched between the insulating enclosure and the plurality of connectors; and


         通过所述中介体的所述多个连接件，将所述第一半导体管芯与所述第二半导体管芯接合在具有多个导电端子的电路结构上，所述电路衬底夹置在所述多个导电端子与所述多个连接件之间。The first semiconductor die and the second semiconductor die are bonded to a circuit structure having a plurality of conductive terminals through the plurality of connectors of the interposer, and the circuit substrate is sandwiched between the plurality of conductive terminals and the plurality of connectors.
